messages.text: Huddled in the living room, Cassie turns to Kinslee.
How do you want to play this?
If they weren‚Äôt standing by the stairs‚Ä¶
You think they‚Äôll recognize us?
I think if we walk right up the stairs, they‚Äôll say something.
I don‚Äôt see anyone else going up there.
So how do we get up there?
I don‚Äôt know.
Wait, I know‚Äî
Back where we came in, I saw another stairwell. It was by the bathroom, out of sight.
Let‚Äôs go that way. I hope Peyton can handle this.
This whole thing will be a disaster if we get caught.
The girls slip around the corner and reach the stairwell without being stopped.
Kinslee notices a door under the stairs.
Look at this ‚Äî maybe they have a basement!
That‚Äôs creepy. See if it‚Äôs open.
No. Locked. Honestly, I‚Äôm kinda glad. I don‚Äôt want to go down there.
Yeah, but what if that‚Äôs Ethan‚Äôs room?
Do you really think we‚Äôre going to find his room?
What if they‚Äôre all locked?
These are frat boys. They‚Äôre not going to lock their rooms when they throw a party in their own house.
Then why is this one locked?
Maybe it‚Äôs storage.
Come on, let‚Äôs just hurry up and get this over with.
Peyton watches as Cassie and Kinslee disappear around the corner.
Her brother is coming towards her, so she makes a choice and walks over to Ethan.
She reaches him just as Mr. Stevens walks away.
God, I hope this works.
Hey, so what are you supposed to be?
Ethan stares down at the clothes he‚Äôs wearing.
Someone who‚Äôs not dressed in a costume.
Oh, so that‚Äôs what you went with? Someone who isn‚Äôt celebrating Halloween?
Yeah, I guess.
You don‚Äôt look like you‚Äôre having fun.
Another aspect of the costume.
Do you live here? At the house?
Yep.
That‚Äôs cool.
Ethan narrows his eyes at her.
He takes a sip from his cup and sighs when he realizes that Peyton isn‚Äôt leaving.
What‚Äôs your costume?
Anime hooker.
Seriously?
Not on purpose. All the zombie nurse costumes were sold out.
You serious?
You‚Äôll never know.
So, you got a name?
Ella.
Ethan blanches, and he takes a step back.
What? You don‚Äôt like my name?
No, you just‚Ä¶excuse me.
Hey, where are you going?
Ethan slides past Peyton and heads for the stairs.
She whips out her phone and texts Cassie and Kinslee.
Guys, he‚Äôs coming.
Shit. We‚Äôre not even up the stairs.
I told him my name was Ella. He freaked.
WHY? Why would you do that?
You did WHAT??
I don‚Äôt know! I think I just wanted to see what he‚Äôd do!
Well now we know!
Hey, we can see him walking down the hall from here. He just went into his room.
Wait and see if he comes back out.
We‚Äôll go in if he leaves.
Okay, I‚Äôll be down here when he does. I‚Äôm going to see if I can find Mr. Stevens again.
It‚Äôs weird, right? Him being here?
Do you think he was here the night of the party? Last week?
No clue. I don‚Äôt know if I can ask him.
Why not?
Cause he‚Äôs our teacher and it‚Äôs weird‚Ä¶
I know I‚Äôm in a costume, but the idea of walking up to him and speaking like I‚Äôm a stranger is freaking me out.
Ethan‚Äôs back. He‚Äôs heading your way.
Okay. I‚Äôll watch for him. Go.
Cassie and Kinslee hurry down to Ethan‚Äôs room. They find the door unlocked and slip inside.
Cassie turns to Kinslee, whispering in the darkness.
Ugh, I can‚Äôt see a thing. Where‚Äôs the light?
I don‚Äôt know, turn on your phone.
This room is a mess.
It‚Äôs a guy‚Äôs room in a frat house ‚Äî what do you expect?
Um, not a biohazard? Here‚Äôs the light switch.
Cassie flips it on.
Wow, it‚Äôs even worse than I thought. How will we find anything in here?
You won‚Äôt, because you‚Äôre leaving. Right now.
Both girls spin around to find Ava lying on the bed, as if she just woke up.
Her eyes are red, and she‚Äôs wearing sweats and a t-shirt.
Ava! What are you doing here?
I think I have more of a right to ask you that question.
Seriously ‚Äî what‚Äôs going on? Really?
We know Ethan was with Ella that night. What happened?
You don‚Äôt know anything.
Why are you acting like this?
You of all people would know that Ella didn‚Äôt overdose. She doesn‚Äôt even take aspirin!
Did Ethan do something to her?
Did he drug her and make it look like an accident?
Stop. You‚Äôve got to stop asking questions.
Ella‚Äôs dead. There‚Äôs nothing that will bring her back.
You act like you don‚Äôt care. She was your sister!
I know that! Don‚Äôt you think I know?
You know something. I think you know Ella didn‚Äôt commit suicide.
It doesn‚Äôt matter what Ella did or didn‚Äôt do. We have to move on.
Ava. You sound afraid. What‚Äôs going on?
Did someone murder her?
You need to leave. Now.
Did Ethan do it?
Ethan didn‚Äôt do anything.
Then why did Mr. Stevens confront him at the funeral home?
He threatened him with the police. He said he had proof!
Ella was in Ethan‚Äôs car, Ava. The police know it.
And they already questioned him and released him.
That doesn‚Äôt mean he‚Äôs innocent.
Kinslee‚Ä¶look.
What?
There, in the corner. That‚Äôs the dress Ella was wearing.
That‚Äôs my dress.
It doesn‚Äôt matter. Ella had it on. I have a picture on my phone to prove it.
I‚Äôm calling my Dad. Ella‚Äôs dress is here. Something happened to her.
Don‚Äôt! You don‚Äôt know what you‚Äôre doing!
Then tell us! What happened?
I can‚Äôt‚Ä¶you need to leave it alone.
Ava, Please.
I‚Ä¶I can‚Äôt.
Ava runs from the room, leaving Kinslee and Cassie alone.
Quick, look around for anything else that belongs to Ella.
We could search for hours and I don‚Äôt think we‚Äôd find everything in here.
Then call your dad ‚Äî just like you said you would. He needs to know that her dress is here.
Maybe there‚Äôs‚Ä¶DNA on it or something.
It still doesn‚Äôt mean anything happened to her, though.
They still think she overdosed at home after Ethan dropped her off.
But we know Ella! We know she would never have done this‚Äî
Something happened, and Ethan knows. So does Ava.
I know. But what can we do? How do we prove it?
We don‚Äôt even know WHAT happened.
Just call your dad. Tell him what we found and see what he says.
Mr. Stevens said something about a camera. Do you see anything like that?
I mean‚Ä¶like what?
The only thing Ethan‚Äôs got on his desk is books and papers. Wait‚Äî
There‚Äôs also a stuffed animal on his dresser‚Ä¶
Grab it. See if there‚Äôs something in there.
Are you kidding? Here, catch ‚Äî since you‚Äôre the expert.
Cassie turns the stuffed animal over in her hands.
Woah, hold on. There‚Äôs Velcro on the back‚Äî
And something inside‚Ä¶oh my god.
What?
It‚Äôs a camera.
Call your dad. Now.
You think it‚Äôs enough?
Kinslee walks over to Ella‚Äôs dress lying on the floor, picks it up and shakes it.
Trust me, this is enough‚Äî
Wait. What just fell out of Ella‚Äôs dress?
Both girls stare down at the syringe lying next to Kinslee‚Äôs feet.
I‚Äôm calling my dad.
